import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout title="Mouse Wheel Plugin">
  <h1>Mouse Wheel</h1>
  <p class="lead">Navigate with the mouse wheel or trackpad. A built-in 300ms debounce prevents accidental multi-slide skips, and axis locking ensures only the correct scroll direction triggers navigation.</p>

  <h2>Import</h2>
  <pre><code>import {"{"} mouseWheel {"}"} from '@andresclua/sliderkit-plugins'</code></pre>

  <h2>Options</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>forceToAxis</code></td><td><code>boolean</code></td><td><code>true</code></td><td>Only trigger navigation when the scroll delta is dominant on the slider's primary axis (horizontal sliders ignore vertical-only scrolls).</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>releaseOnEdges</code></td><td><code>boolean</code></td><td>—</td><td>Reserved option — present in the interface but not yet implemented.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>sensitivity</code></td><td><code>number</code></td><td><code>1</code></td><td>Multiplier applied to the raw delta. A negative value inverts the scroll direction.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Example</h2>
  <pre><code>{`import { createSlider } from '@andresclua/sliderkit'
import { mouseWheel } from '@andresclua/sliderkit-plugins'

createSlider('#my-slider', {
  plugins: [
    mouseWheel({
      forceToAxis: true,
      sensitivity: 1,
    }),
  ],
})`}</code></pre>

  <p>The plugin attaches a non-passive <code>wheel</code> event listener and calls <code>e.preventDefault()</code> on qualifying events to prevent the page from scrolling while navigating the slider.</p>

  <p><a href="/demos/mousewheel">View mouse wheel demo</a></p>
</DocsLayout>
